{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Preheat oven to 180°C. Grease and line a 12-hole muffin tray with cupcake liners and set aside.","Place apple into mixing bowl and chop <b>3 sec\/speed 7<b>. Transfer into a bowl and set aside.","Place 90 g butter into mixing bowl and melt <b>1-2 min 30 sec\/60°C\/speed 1<b>, until butter has melted.","Add egg, milk, flour, honey, cinnamon and brown sugar and combine <b>5 sec\/speed 5<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add reserved apple and combine <b>5 sec\/\/speed 4<b>. Spoon mixture into prepared muffin tray. Cut the top and bottom off the 2 extra unpeeled apples, then cut each apple into 6 rounds (approx. 5 mm thick). Gently place 1 slice on top of each muffin.","Bake for 20-25 minutes (180°C) or until a wooden skewer inserted into the centre of a muffin comes out clean. Transfer muffins onto a wire rack to cool (approx. 20 minutes) then serve."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["90 g butter, cut into pieces, plus extra for greasing","150 g Granny Smith apples, peeled and cut into quarters, plus 2 extra apples, unpeeled, for garnishing","1 egg","180 g full cream milk","250 g self-raising flour","1 tbsp honey","1 tsp ground cinnamon","100 g brown sugar"]}],"id":"r78742","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-fIJeXUFAOrs\/XZafPYLiiPI\/AAAAAAAAgsg\/6myuQ1NuEAglMKsuxmsoAF1VdCGnQDliwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_k-1gpyNQD-Dxt6Ig.png","title":"Apple and cinnamon muffins","publishedAt":"2015-08-07T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"3.5 g","fat":"7.3 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"29 g","calories":"821 kJ \/ 195 kcal"},"usefulItems":"12-hole muffin tray, cupcake liners, wire rack, wooden skewer, bowl, oven","hintsAndTricks":["These quick and easy muffins are so simple you can make them every week. Omit the apple slice garnishes to make these muffins even faster and simpler if desired."],"basicInfo":["easy","10m","35m","12 portions"]}